Beats include racial justice, immigration, women's empowerment, activism, and the Asian American community. My documentary created for NBC News titled "Deported," follows the grassroots fight to end deportation of Cambodian Americans from the U.S. to Cambodia. I led a crew to film in four U.S. cities and abroad in Phnom Penh, Cambodia, capturing a historical meeting between activists, deportees, and the Cambodian government in a discussion to revise the Repatriation Agreement between the two countries and end deportation. “Deported” won the 2018 NAMIC Vision Award for Best Digital Media, Long Form (The National Association for Multi-Ethnicity in Communications), beating out CNN’s Lisa Ling.My documentary series for NBC News, “Self-Starters,” celebrates Asian American trailblazers around the country. “Self-Starters” was the first series to launched the video platform for NBC Asian America and was nominated for the LA Press Club and EPPY Awards alongside TIME, CNN, and ESPN. Both of my parents are Vietnamese refugees who fled Vietnam by boat after the war. I'm here to create world-shifting narratives. Let's work together!
